    <briefdescription>
<para>Write-only buffer for accumulating messages in a double-buffered system. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para><ref refid="classhelios_1_1core_1_1data_1_1WriteBuffer" kindref="compound">WriteBuffer</ref> is the producer-side of a double-buffered message system. Messages are pushed to this buffer during frame processing, then swapped with a <ref refid="classhelios_1_1core_1_1data_1_1ReadBuffer" kindref="compound">ReadBuffer</ref> at frame boundaries. This separation enables lock-free, single-threaded producer-consumer patterns.</para>
<para>The internal storage is only accessible to <ref refid="classhelios_1_1core_1_1data_1_1ReadWriteDoubleBuffer" kindref="compound">ReadWriteDoubleBuffer</ref> for swap operations.</para>
<para><parameterlist kind="templateparam"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>T</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>The message type stored in the buffer. Must be move-constructible. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
</para>
    </detaileddescription>
